<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: compound_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context"><p>A <b>compound_maths_space_context</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>

 that is defined by a list of other instances of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.

The referenced <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>

 is a space of tuples. The <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>

 for each item in a tuple has the corresponding position in the list.</p>
<example>Consider two different instances of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>, as follows:</example>
<p>P<sub>1</sub>: the relationship between the 2D set of points on the surface of 'my product' and R<sup>2</sup>; and</p> 
<p>P<sub>2</sub>:the relationship between the 1D set of states in 'my activity' and R. </p>
<p>The relationship between</p>
<ul><li>the 3D set of set of points on the surface of 'my product' for the states in 'my activity', and</li>
<li>
R<sup>3</sup>,
</li></ul>
<p>is the <b>compound_maths_space_context</b> defined by P1 x P2.</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: compound_maths_space_context  Attribute: components 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context.components"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.compound_maths_space_context.components"><p>the instances of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/> that are components of the <b>compound_maths_space_context</b>.   A <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>  for a single state of a product can be derived from the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>  of the product. In this case the single state shall have a <b>compound_maths_space_context</b> with a components list consisting of a single reference to the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>  of the product.
</p></ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: defined_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context"><p>A <b>defined_maths_space_context</b> is a type of  <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>  that is defined by reference to a <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_context"/>, <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.unit"/> or both.</p>
<note>A <b>defined_maths_space_context</b>  can be instantiated as a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context"/>, a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context"/> or both.
</note></ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context"><p>An <b>explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>

 that is defined by specifying the instances of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>

 that are members of the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.</p> 
<note>An <b>explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context</b> can only be specified for a discrete <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>

 with a finite number of members.
</note></ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context  Attribute: members 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context.members"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.explicitly_enumerated_maths_space_context.members">the instances of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>

 that are members of the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context">
A <b>maths_space_context</b> is a 1-1 mapping between a physical space and a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>

 that indicates a meaning for the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.id">
the <express_ref linkend="support_resource_schema:ir_express:support_resource_schema.identifier"/>

 for the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.name">
the <express_ref linkend="support_resource_schema:ir_express:support_resource_schema.label"/>

 by which the <b>maths_space_context</b> is known.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.description">
the <express_ref linkend="support_resource_schema:ir_express:support_resource_schema.text"/> that characterizes the  <b>maths_space_context</b>. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: abstract_space 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.abstract_space"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.abstract_space"><p>the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>

 that has each member corresponding to one member of the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.physical_space"/>.
</p>
<note number="1">This schema references the ABSTRACT entity type <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>

 from ISO 10303-50, but not an entity type that is a SUBTYPE. An Application Module that uses this part of ISO 10303 should reference or define at least one SUBTYPE.</note>
<note number="2">Each of the subtypes of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_function"/>

 defined in ISO 10303-50 requires that a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>

 be a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.tuple_space"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_space_context  Attribute: physical_space 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.physical_space"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.physical_space">
the physical space that has each member corresponding to one members of the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context.abstract_space"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_value_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context">A <b>maths_value_context</b> is an association between a physical value and a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_space"/>.

  A meaning assigned to a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_value"/>  by such an association can be deduced from a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>

 that has the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>  as a member.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_value_context  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.id">
the <express_ref linkend="support_resource_schema:ir_express:support_resource_schema.identifier"/>

 for the <b>maths_value_context</b>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_value_context  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.name">
the <express_ref linkend="support_resource_schema:ir_express:support_resource_schema.label"/>

 by which the <b>maths_value_context</b> is known.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_value_context  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.description">
the <express_ref linkend="support_resource_schema:ir_express:support_resource_schema.text"/> that characterizes the  <b>maths_value_context</b>.  The value of this attribute need not be specified.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_value_context  Attribute: abstract_value 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.abstract_value"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.abstract_value">
the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_value"/>

 that corresponds to the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.physical_value"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: maths_value_context  Attribute: physical_value 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.physical_value"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context.physical_value">
the physical value that corresponds to the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_functions_schema:ir_express:mathematical_functions_schema.maths_value"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: membership_of_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context">
A <b>membership_of_maths_space_context</b> is an association between a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>

 and a <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>

 that indicates the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>  is a member of the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: membership_of_maths_space_context  Attribute: space_context 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context.space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context.space_context">
the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>

 that has the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>

 as a member.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: membership_of_maths_space_context  Attribute: value_context 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context.value_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.membership_of_maths_space_context.value_context">
the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_value_context"/>

 that is a member of the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: normalized_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context"><p>A <b>normalized_maths_space_context</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context"/>
 that is defined by a reference physical value.</p>

<p>Let:</p>

<p>p be a physical value;
</p>
<p>
p<sub>0</sub> be the reference physical value;
</p>
<p>
v be the maths value.
</p>
<p>
An instance of <b>normalized_maths_space_context</b> specifies that:
</p><p>
p = p<sub>0</sub>.v</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: normalized_maths_space_context  Attribute: normalization_basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context.normalization_basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.normalized_maths_space_context.normalization_basis">
the reference physical value that defines the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: representation_context_defined_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context">
A <b>representation_context_defined_maths_space_context</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context"/> that specifies a coordinate system. It is defined by reference to a <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_context"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: representation_context_defined_maths_space_context  Attribute: representation_basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context.representation_basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.representation_context_defined_maths_space_context.representation_basis">
 the <express_ref linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_context"/>

 that defines the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: unit_defined_maths_space_context  
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context">
A <b>unit_defined_maths_space_context</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.defined_maths_space_context"/>

 that is defined by a single unit of measure.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: mathematical_context_schema  Entity: unit_defined_maths_space_context  Attribute: unit_basis 
   <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema::mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context.unit_basis"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="mathematical_context_schema.unit_defined_maths_space_context.unit_basis"><p>the unit that defines the <express_ref linkend="mathematical_context_schema:ir_express:mathematical_context_schema.maths_space_context"/>. </p>
<note>This schema references the SELECT type unit from ISO 10303-41, but not the entity types that are selected by unit. An Application Module that uses this part of ISO 10303 should reference at least one of these entity types.</note>
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
